#: ../../../appendix/building-from-source.md:19
msgid "Clone the repository"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../appendix/building-from-source.md:21
msgid ""
"git clone https://github.com/NVlabs/cuda-oxide.git\n"
"cd cuda-oxide\n"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../appendix/building-from-source.md:26
msgid "Install the Rust toolchain"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../appendix/building-from-source.md:28
msgid ""
"The repo ships a `rust-toolchain.toml` that pins the exact nightly version "
"and components. Rustup picks it up automatically:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../appendix/building-from-source.md:31
msgid ""
"# rust-toolchain.toml (already in the repo root)\n"
"[toolchain]\n"
"channel = \"nightly-2026-04-03\"\n"
"components = [\"rust-src\", \"rustc-dev\", \"rust-analyzer\", \"clippy\", "
"\"llvm-tools\"]\n"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../appendix/building-from-source.md:38
msgid "If you need to install manually:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../appendix/building-from-source.md:40
msgid ""
"rustup toolchain install nightly-2026-04-03\n"
"rustup component add rust-src rustc-dev --toolchain nightly-2026-04-03\n"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../appendix/building-from-source.md:45
msgid ""
"`rust-src` provides the standard library source for cross-compilation and "
"`rustc-dev` exposes compiler internals that the codegen backend links "
"against."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../appendix/building-from-source.md:48
msgid "Install CUDA"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../appendix/building-from-source.md:50
msgid "Make sure the CUDA toolkit is on your `PATH`:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../appendix/building-from-source.md:52
msgid ""
"export PATH=\"/usr/local/cuda/bin:$PATH\"\n"
"nvcc --version   # should print 12.x or later\n"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../appendix/building-from-source.md:57
msgid ""
"If you are building on a system without a GPU (e.g. CI), the toolkit is "
"still required for `ptxas` and header files, but you will not be able to run "
"kernels."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../appendix/building-from-source.md:60
msgid "Install LLVM (usually optional)"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../appendix/building-from-source.md:62
msgid ""
"The codegen pipeline emits LLVM IR and invokes `llc` to produce PTX. The "
"pinned Rust toolchain (`nightly-2026-04-03`) already ships LLVM 22 with the "
"NVPTX backend enabled via the `llvm-tools` component, so the recommended "
"path is:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../appendix/building-from-source.md:67
msgid "rustup component add llvm-tools\n"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../appendix/building-from-source.md:71
msgid ""
"The component is already listed in `rust-toolchain.toml`, so on a fresh "
"clone rustup installs it automatically; running the command above is the one-"
"shot fix for older clones. The pipeline auto-detects this `llc` at "
"`<sysroot>/lib/rustlib/<host>/bin/llc`."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../appendix/building-from-source.md:76
msgid ""
"If you would rather use a system LLVM (for a specific patch level, or "
"because you already have one installed), the pipeline falls back to "
"`llc-22` / `llc-21` on `PATH`. LLVM 21 is the minimum — earlier releases "
"reject the TMA / tcgen05 / WGMMA intrinsic signatures that cuda-oxide emits."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../appendix/building-from-source.md:82
msgid ""
"# Ubuntu / Debian\n"
"sudo apt install llvm-21\n"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../appendix/building-from-source.md:87
msgid ""
"If your distro packages do not provide `llvm-21`, use LLVM's apt helper:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../appendix/building-from-source.md:89
msgid ""
"sudo apt-get install -y lsb-release wget software-properties-common gnupg\n"
"wget https://apt.llvm.org/llvm.sh && chmod +x llvm.sh\n"
"sudo ./llvm.sh 21\n"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../appendix/building-from-source.md:95
msgid ""
"# Verify NVPTX support\n"
"llc-21 --version | grep nvptx\n"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../appendix/building-from-source.md:100
msgid "You should see `nvptx64 - NVIDIA PTX 64-bit` in the target list."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../appendix/building-from-source.md:102
msgid ""
"To pin a specific binary (rustup's, a distro's, or a custom build), set "
"`CUDA_OXIDE_LLC=/path/to/llc`. The pipeline's full resolution order is:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../appendix/building-from-source.md:105
msgid "`$CUDA_OXIDE_LLC` (if set)"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../appendix/building-from-source.md:106
msgid "The Rust toolchain's `llvm-tools` llc"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../appendix/building-from-source.md:107
msgid "`llc-22`, then `llc-21`, then bare `llc` on `PATH`"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../appendix/building-from-source.md:110
msgid ""
"Older `llc` binaries (LLVM 20 and earlier) will compile simpler kernels when "
"pointed at via `CUDA_OXIDE_LLC=/path/to/llc-20`, but any example that uses "
"modern TMA / tcgen05 / WGMMA intrinsics (`tma_copy`, `gemm_sol`, "
"`tcgen05_matmul`, `wgmma`, …) will fail with `Intrinsic has incorrect "
"argument type!` until you upgrade to LLVM 21+."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../appendix/building-from-source.md:117
msgid "Install Clang (for host `cuda-bindings`)"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../appendix/building-from-source.md:119
msgid ""
"The host `cuda-bindings` crate runs `bindgen`, which loads libclang and "
"needs clang's own resource-dir `stddef.h` — a bare `libclang1-*` runtime is "
"not enough."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../appendix/building-from-source.md:123
msgid "sudo apt install clang-21   # or libclang-common-21-dev\n"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../appendix/building-from-source.md:127
msgid "`cargo oxide doctor` verifies this up front."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../appendix/building-from-source.md:129
msgid "Build the workspace"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../appendix/building-from-source.md:131
msgid ""
"The main workspace contains the user-facing crates (`cuda-device`, `cuda-"
"core`, `cuda-async`, etc.) and the build tooling (`cargo-oxide`):"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../appendix/building-from-source.md:134
msgid "cargo build\n"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../appendix/building-from-source.md:139
msgid ""
"The codegen backend (`crates/rustc-codegen-cuda/`) is intentionally **not** "
"a workspace member because it requires special nightly features and a "
"different build process. `cargo-oxide` handles building it transparently."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../appendix/building-from-source.md:144
msgid "Install cargo-oxide"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../appendix/building-from-source.md:146
msgid ""
"`cargo-oxide` is the cargo subcommand that drives the full compilation "
"pipeline. Inside the repo, it works via a workspace alias. For standalone "
"use, install it with the pinned nightly toolchain:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../appendix/building-from-source.md:149
msgid ""
"cargo +nightly-2026-04-03 install --git https://github.com/NVlabs/cuda-oxide."
"git cargo-oxide\n"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../appendix/building-from-source.md:153
msgid ""
"On first run, `cargo-oxide` automatically fetches and builds the codegen "
"backend dylib."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../appendix/building-from-source.md:156
msgid "Verify the installation"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../appendix/building-from-source.md:158
msgid ""
"# Check all prerequisites\n"
"cargo oxide doctor\n"
"\n"
"# Compile and run the canonical first example\n"
"cargo oxide run vecadd\n"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../appendix/building-from-source.md:166
msgid ""
"`cargo oxide doctor` validates your Rust toolchain, CUDA toolkit (including "
"libNVVM / nvJitLink / libdevice for kernels that use math intrinsics), LLVM "
"installation, and codegen backend. If everything is configured correctly, "
"`cargo oxide run vecadd` compiles a Rust kernel to PTX, launches it on the "
"GPU, and prints a success message."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../appendix/building-from-source.md:172
msgid "Common commands"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../appendix/building-from-source.md:174
msgid ""
"# Build and run an example\n"
"cargo oxide run <example>\n"
"\n"
"# Show the full compilation pipeline (MIR → LLVM IR → PTX)\n"
"cargo oxide pipeline <example>\n"
"\n"
"# Run under NVIDIA Compute Sanitizer\n"
"cargo oxide sanitize <example> --tool memcheck\n"
"\n"
"# Debug with cuda-gdb\n"
"cargo oxide debug <example> --tui\n"
"\n"
"# Build NVVM IR for libNVVM/nvJitLink interop\n"
"cargo oxide build <example> --emit-nvvm-ir --arch sm_120\n"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../appendix/building-from-source.md:191
msgid "Building the book"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../appendix/building-from-source.md:193
msgid ""
"The documentation lives in `cuda-oxide-book/` and uses Sphinx with MyST "
"Markdown. To build and serve locally:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../appendix/building-from-source.md:196
msgid ""
"cd cuda-oxide-book\n"
"make setup      # creates venv, installs dependencies\n"
"source .venv/bin/activate\n"
"make livehtml   # starts dev server on http://localhost:8000\n"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../appendix/building-from-source.md:203
msgid "Generating API documentation"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../appendix/building-from-source.md:205
msgid "Standard `cargo doc` works for the workspace crates:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../appendix/building-from-source.md:207
msgid "cargo doc --no-deps --open\n"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../appendix/building-from-source.md:211
msgid ""
"This generates rustdoc for `cuda-device`, `cuda-core`, `cuda-async`, and all "
"other workspace members. The codegen backend is excluded since it is not a "
"workspace member."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../appendix/building-from-source.md:215
msgid "Workspace structure"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../appendix/building-from-source.md:217
msgid ""
"cuda-oxide/\n"
"├── Cargo.toml              # Workspace root\n"
"├── rust-toolchain.toml     # Pinned nightly + components\n"
"├── crates/\n"
"│   ├── cuda-device/          # Device intrinsics (#![no_std])\n"
"│   ├── cuda-host/            # Host launch APIs\n"
"│   ├── cuda-macros/          # Proc macros (#[kernel], #[device], "
"gpu_printf!)\n"
"│   ├── cuda-bindings/        # Raw bindgen FFI to cuda.h\n"
"│   ├── cuda-core/            # Safe RAII wrappers (CudaContext, "
"DeviceBuffer)\n"
"│   ├── cuda-async/           # Async execution (DeviceOperation, "
"DeviceFuture)\n"
"│   ├── cargo-oxide/          # Cargo subcommand\n"
"│   ├── rustc-codegen-cuda/   # Codegen backend (not a workspace member)\n"
"│   ├── mir-importer/         # MIR → Pliron IR translation\n"
"│   ├── mir-lower/            # `dialect-mir` → LLVM dialect lowering\n"
"│   ├── dialect-mir/          # pliron dialect modelling Rust MIR\n"
"│   ├── llvm-export/          # shim re-exporting pliron-llvm + textual .ll "
"export\n"
"│   ├── dialect-nvvm/         # NVVM intrinsics dialect\n"
"│   ├── libnvvm-sys/          # dlopen bindings to libNVVM\n"
"│   ├── nvjitlink-sys/        # dlopen bindings to nvJitLink\n"
"│   ├── reserved-oxide-symbols/ # Shared naming contract\n"
"│   └── fuzzer/               # Differential testing support\n"
"└── cuda-oxide-book/        # This book (Sphinx + MyST)\n"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../appendix/building-from-source.md:242
msgid "Troubleshooting"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../appendix/building-from-source.md:244
msgid "`llc` not found or missing NVPTX"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../appendix/building-from-source.md:245
msgid ""
"The fastest fix is `rustup component add llvm-tools` — the pinned "
"toolchain's `llc` is LLVM 22 with NVPTX enabled and is auto-picked up. "
"Otherwise install a system LLVM 21+ (`sudo apt install llvm-21`); the "
"pipeline probes the rustup `llc` first, then `llc-22` → `llc-21` on `PATH`. "
"To pin a specific binary set `CUDA_OXIDE_LLC=/path/to/llc`."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../appendix/building-from-source.md:251
msgid "`Intrinsic has incorrect argument type!` (from `llc`)"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../appendix/building-from-source.md:252
msgid ""
"Your `llc` is older than LLVM 21 and cannot lower the modern TMA / tcgen05 / "
"WGMMA intrinsic signatures. Install `llvm-21` and re-run."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../appendix/building-from-source.md:255
msgid "`error[E0463]: can't find crate for rustc_middle`"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../appendix/building-from-source.md:256
msgid ""
"You are missing the `rustc-dev` component. Run: `rustup component add rustc-"
"dev --toolchain nightly-2026-04-03`."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../appendix/building-from-source.md:259
msgid "CUDA driver version mismatch"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../appendix/building-from-source.md:260
msgid ""
"The toolkit version (compile-time) and driver version (runtime) must be "
"compatible. Run `nvidia-smi` to check the driver version, and `nvcc --"
"version` for the toolkit."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../appendix/building-from-source.md:264
msgid "`cargo oxide doctor` fails on codegen backend"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../appendix/building-from-source.md:265
msgid ""
"The backend is built on first use. If the build fails, check that `rust-src` "
"is installed and that the nightly version matches `rust-toolchain.toml`."
msgstr ""
